This paper is about automated rationale generation, which is a technique for explainable AI. It involves training a neural rationale generator to produce natural language explanations for an autonomous agent's behavior. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), machine learning (cs.LG), and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, and cs.RO, in that order.
